Author: AaronD
Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: Several days ago I had the misfortune of creating an account on this exchange and deposing Substratum to my account. Due to other issues, I was not able to deposit BTC to pay for the selling fees,  and when I attempted to withdraw my Substratum I ran into several problems that are a cause for concern.  This exchange requires you to upload sensitive documents to verify your identity, otherwise you have a daily withdraw limit of $100 USD. This fact was not made clear when signing up for the exchange, and I do not trust CoinPlace's security measures to be sufficient enough to keep my personal information secure.  There is also the fact that their "Terms and Conditions" state that some jurisdictions are restricted from using CoinPlace, but they do not include which jurisdictions are restricted.  I no longer wish to use this exchange, but my funds are being withheld from me unless I willingly upload highly sensitive documents to a website with highly questionable security. Coinplace lacks basic security measures, has a terrible UI, lacks some of the most basics features standard among other exchanges, and after trying twice to contact their support I was unable to get through or receive any assistance.  I fear that this exchange is a scam, and that my funds are gone. I have sent an email and a message to them on this forum, but I have received no response.

Body: 0% COMMISSIONS ON OPERATIONS WITH CRYPTOCURRENCIES  The countries that chose to prohibit all and any operations with cryptocurrencies donâ€™t give up their ground. However, this is to the advantage of the countries that favor Bitcoins, e.g. European states that do not charge any commissions on Bitcoin transactions. Yes, they do exist, and now itâ€™s time to talk about them.   ğŸ‡©ğŸ‡ªGermany  In Germany cryptocurrencies are not considered either a commodity or a currency. They are viewed as private funds, just like foreign currencies. Bitcoin transactions are categorized as private trading, and any trader is completely exempt of any taxes until capital gains exceed 600 EUR. If a trader sells his or her cryptoassets within a year or more, all gains are also covered by tax exemptions.   ğŸ‡©ğŸ‡°Denmark  Denmark is one of the most crypto-friendly countries in the world, and no Bitcoin transactions there are taxable. This means neither generosity, no ignorance: the government of Denmark is making a serious attempt to develop the first cash-free economy in the world.   ğŸ‡¸ğŸ‡®Slovenia  This country is yet another tax harbor for individual investors: capital gain is not taxable and is not considered a part of personal income. However, for corporate income the tax is charged.  Still, if we think about all bans and prohibitions associated with Bitcoin, this looks quite good, doesnâ€™t it?

Author: filsid
Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: The most popular Questions and Answers  1. How can I buy CPL tokens? If you want to buy CPL tokens for cryptocurrency: You go to CoinPlace.info, press Buy CPL-Tokens in the right upper corner. You will be taken to the registration page. Here you start creating your account. You type in your email address and a password. After the registration process is completed, you are automatically logged into your account. There you will see three main tabs: Invested (the CPL tokens amount you have already bought), Bonus (awarded and can be seen after the token purchase and depends on the amount and at which ICO stage you bought them), Raised during ICO (how much money was raised to this point excluding the closed presale). Right under the â€œRaised during ICOâ€ button, you will see the button â€œBuy nowâ€. After pressing it, you need to choose between two payment methods: crypto or fiat. Choose â€œcryptoâ€. Then you choose the cryptocurrency you hold. Then you type in the sum, and you will see how much CPL tokens you can buy for the amount of crypro you have. Lower you will see an address of the wallet YOU NEED TO TRANSWER YOUR ASSETS to receive our tokens. The process is automatic. In order to do this you need to have a wallet that supports ERC20 type tokens. You go to your wallet and transfer the crypto you chose from the list in your CoinPlace account to the address you copied from our website, and in return you receive our tokens. Coins will be transferred to your wallet on our platform. They can be transferred to any wallet supporting ERC20 in 5 days after the end of ICO.  If you want to buy CPL tokens for fiat money: You go to CoinPlace.info, press Buy CPL-Tokens in the right upper corner. You will be taken to the registration page. Here you start creating your account. You type in your email address and a password. After the registration process is completed, you are automatically logged into your account. There you will see three main tabs: Invested (the CPL tokens amount you have already bought), Bonus (awarded and can be seen after the token purchase and depends on the amount and at which ICO stage you bought them), Raised during ICO (how much money was raised to this point excluding the closed presale). Right under the â€œRaised during ICOâ€ button, you will see the button â€œBuy nowâ€. After pressing it, you need to choose between two payment methods: crypto or fiat. Choose â€œfiatâ€. Lower you will see the button â€œBuy CPL nowâ€. This will take you to another websiteâ€Šâ€”â€Šour platform, where you will see a list of sellers. Every seller will specify his own terms of sale (acceptable payment methods, limits and prices). You need to choose a suitable seller and press â€œBuyâ€ with the sellerâ€™s nick. Then you will need to accept the terms and conditions and press Accept. You will see your order after that. There will be two lines: â€œSendingâ€ on the left (there you type in the amount in the currency you want to pay with) and â€œPayingâ€ on the right (there you will see the amount of CPL tokens you can buy for the amount you want to spend). Lower you will see your bonus (if you are eligible to it) awarded for your purchase. Lower you will see a line where you can type in your comment for the seller. Then you press Submit Request, which will be under the comments line. As soon as you press this button, your trade starts. Then you wait for the sellerâ€™s reply. A chat window will open, where the seller will type in his details (if they are not listed). You will use the details to transfer the money. Then the seller will transfer tokens to your wallet on CoinPlace.pro  2. How can I cancel my deal with a seller? After you have chosen a seller, typed in the sum and pressed Submit Request under the comments line, you are taken to the page detailing the deal process. There you will see the button â€œCancelâ€ on the left. Your deal will be cancelled as soon as you press the button.  3. Can I get my money back if I have already transferred it to the seller? In this case, you cannot. The seller might act at his own discretion.  4. How do I register? You go to CoinPlace.info and press Buy CPL-Tokens. The registration window opens. You will only need to type in your email address and create a password to register.  5. What is fiat money? Fiat Money is the currency that a government established as a legal payment method in spite of the fact that it does not have any intrinsic value and is not backed by commodities. Historically, most of the currencies were created from goods like gold or silver. Fiat money on the contrary has an assigned value only due to the trust in the state. Today most paper money in the world is fiat money.  6. Why do I need two different accounts on CoinPlace.pro and CCoinPlace.info? After you have created an account on CoinPlace.pro, your wallet is linked to this account. Using this account you can only buy CPL tokens for fiat money. After you have created an account on CoinPlace.info, you will see the amount of CPL tokens you currently hold. Using this account, you can only buy CPL tokens for crypto.  7. How can I find my wallet? On CoinPlace.pro: You need to log into your account on the platform. In order to do that you need to press Sign In in the right upper corner of the main page. Press it and register or log into your account, then you will be automatically taken to the tab â€œWalletsâ€. In the left part of the screen you will see the amount of tokens you hold. You can click it to see the details of your previous transactions. You will have an option to transfer tokens using an address or a nickname. On CoinPlace.info: When you log into your account, you are taken to the page â€œParticipate in ICOâ€. There you will see your token balance.  8. How can I withdraw my tokens and which wallets can I transfer them to? If your tokens are on CoinPlace.info, you will be able to transfer them only in 5 days after the end of ICO.  9. What is the difference between info and pro websites? CoinPlace.info is strictly an ICO site, while CoinPlace.pro is the platform itself.  10. Why do I need your tokens? You will be able to pay for the following services with CPL tokens on the platform: à¹ posting ads on the platform (ICO, cryptocurrency services and websites, mining equipment, selling cryptocurrency for fiat money); à¹ listing ICO tokens on the platform (as a listing fee); à¹ priority service on our website (for example, expedited verification or arbitration, etc.); à¹ moving your ads to the top; à¹ a special status.  11. How can I sell other ICO tokens on your platform? To sell another projectâ€™s ICO tokens, you need to list them first on our platform. However, this feature is not available yet. You can only transfer CPL tokens using the platform and only using a nickname.  12. Can I list bitcoins on your platform? Not at the moment, but this service will be available by the end of January.  13. How much does your token cost? Our token costs 0,001 ETH.   14. Will your token be listed on exchanges? What is the pricing mechanism? Yes, our token will be listed on various exchanges in one or two weeks after ICO. The number of tokens will decrease over time, which will raise the token value. Our platform is a functioning product. This will also contribute to the stable value increase of the token.  15. How much is your token worth in euros? Some of the sellers on our platform are from Europe, and they sell tokens only for euros. Yu can find them in the list of sellers and check prices in euros.  16. When can I sell tokens? You can sell tokens in 5 days after the end of ICO.  17. How can I buy tokens using a credit card? Some of the sellers on our platform accept payments to their bankcards. You can find them in the list of sellers on our platform.  18. How long does a transaction take? After the deal has been approved by the seller, the transaction takes up to 5 minutes.  Check for updates at our website and in social media! Join Pre-ICO and test the platform in action: www.coinplace.pro  Pre-ICO stage: December 5â€Šâ€”â€ŠJanuar 31 2018 ICO stage: February 2018 (the exact date will be announced later)  https://medium.com/@CoinPlacePro/the-most-popular-questions-and-answers-a616084626c2

Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: Well, this is rather convenient. Do you want do buy or to sell crypt? Actually, there's no difference â€” the system is the same, anyway. Whoever wants to buy or sell the asset, places a bet (bid or offer) into the system. I saw Coinplace announcing hidden dashboards for bigger pool deals but here we're talking about the open part.  So, when there is a match between the two sides, i.e. buyer and seller, the deal is done. Technically, the one who has crypt on his/her hands, places it in a custody (escrow). And the other side transfers fiat. When fiat is received, the "crypt" side unlocks the escrow.

Body: COINPLACE PLATFORM ANNOUNCES A NEW PRE-ICO DATE   The CoinPlace team rescheduled the start of Pre-ICO in order to improve platform usability. Other companies rarely launch ICO let alone Pre-ICO without MVP. Rather than offering our investors just an idea of a project, a blind bargain, we would like to present a fully functioning platform.   CTO of CoinPlace Alexander Sakagansky said, â€œBefore launching Pre-ICO we unexpectedly discovered that we probably went overboard, and currently our service is not as easy to use as we would like. We ourselves do not like it when processes are too complicated as if they were designed for crypto geeks. That is why we made a difficult decision to postpone our ICO for a week and use this time to improve the service interface making it more user-friendly. So that anyone could figure it out in less than a minute, even if he is buying cryptocurrency or tokens for the first time in his life.â€   It will take the team 4-5 days to improve the interface.     CoinPlace Pre-ICO will start December 5th at 6 pm GMT+3.   Follow our news and join us! You can already register as an early investor here: www.coinplace.info

LocalBitcoins, LocalEthereum, LocalMonero, Paxful, Qvolta and Cryptolocator work only with 2 key currencies (Bitcoin and Etherium). Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: Protection from attacks: we protect and test the site for vulnerabilities using third-party services (for example, Defectify). CloudFlare protects against DDoS and other network hacking methods. Cluster system of servers: even if one or several servers fail or hacked, the cluster system will help the service to work without failures. Servers are located in different countries and data centers to improve data security. In this way, we provide maximum protection to our customers.

Author: CoinPlacePro
Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: CoinPlace acts as the guarantor of p2p exchange between the participants of transactions. The service will lock up crypto currency funds until the transaction is confirmed by the seller and the buyer. In case of a dispute, the funds are not returned to the parties to the transaction until they reach a mutual agreement. If the parties do not reach an agreement, either party may fill a request for consideration of the transaction by the platform's arbiter. The disputed transaction is moderated by the platform arbiter. Its task is to request a set of data from each of the users to make a decision about whether the payment of fiat money was made. The result of the dispute is the transfer of digital assets to one of the parties, as well as a change in the rating of the party guilty of arbitration.

Author: Cryggdrasil
Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: Obviously, it has some correlation with ETH dynamics. After Ethereum jumped 10 times, those who had large chunks acquired basically for free, started unloading with little or no control simply seeding capital and planting growth everywhere possible. And now this seem no longer the case, new investors either bought their ETH expensively, or mined it (again, with higher capex and opex).  So, no more free money. That is why projects are under much deeper analysis now. And don't forget about competition -- supply of tokens is simply enormous these days, with little or no MVPs behind. So, everyone is watching carefully for gems to be found in tons of mud.

Author: Cryggdrasil
Title: ğŸš€[ANN][ICO]ğŸš€Coinplace:ğŸ”¥The first in the world platform for direct P2PğŸ”¥
Body: Well, this is rather convenient. Do you want do buy or to sell crypt? Actually, there's no difference â€” the system is the same, anyway. Whoever wants to buy or sell the asset, places a bet (bid or offer) into the system. I saw Coinplace announcing hidden dashboards for bigger pool deals but here we're talking about the open part.  So, when there is a match between the two sides, i.e. buyer and seller, the deal is done. Technically, the one who has crypt on his/her hands, places it in a custody (escrow). And the other side transfers fiat. When fiat is received, the "crypt" side unlocks the escrow.

Body: We are following all country specific legislation. Coinplace doesnot get involved in trading and provides no platform or place for such. From the business point of view, we are a marketplace that serves interest of all counterparties and uses its abilities to improve conditions for peer-to-peer deals. We are closely monitoring all regulations and restrictions and never brake any laws. Swaps that are made are direct exchange operations between our clients, and unless directly prohibited, they don't violate general principles of free trade and exchange. Obviously, there are certain risks in the area and we, for example, recommend everyone to act in full accordance with local tax regime and remain within the taxation framework. All deal are held at the customer's discression. The system may guarantee you from the other party's unfair behaviour, thus in case all conditions are met, the deal will proceed.
